one that the Theravada line holds, which is the one that we would normally refer to, and they're normally called suttas or discourses.

98
00:09:33,667 --> 00:09:47,081
But there was a whole load that were preserved in the Chinese of a line of a school of Buddhism called the Savastavardins, and they're known as the Agamas.

99
00:09:47,533 --> 00:09:59,304
and they've now been translated and studied, and they are very, you might say they are compatible with, definitely, and a companion to.

100
00:09:59,845 --> 00:10:08,332
So the Buddha, in the numerical discourses that we have, has two discourses on death, how to do contemplation on death.

101
